%N A394944 Number of well-formed bracketed words of total length n built from the symbol * (of length 1) and four unary bracket types (), [], {}, and <>, with no empty bracket pair, where every maximal chain of unary brackets is written in canonical weakly increasing order.
%C A394944 a(0)=1 counts the empty word.
%C A394944 For n>=1, a(n)=b_{4,1}^c(n) in the notation of Au and Bremner; see Section 3.
%C A394944 Equivalently, a(n) counts canonical representatives of such bracketed words under commutativity of the four unary bracket types.
%C A394944 In each maximal chain of nested unary brackets, the bracket types are weakly increasing from outermost to innermost.
%C A394944 Equivalently, a(n) counts rooted ordered trees in which each leaf represents *, each unary internal node is labeled 1, 2, 3, or 4, every non-unary internal node has at least 2 ordered children, and the labels along every maximal unary chain are weakly increasing from the root toward the leaves.
%C A394944 Equivalently, a(n) counts peakless Motzkin paths of length n with four types of up-steps U_1, U_2, U_3, U_4, such that along every matched ascent the labels are weakly increasing.
%C A394944 Here a matched ascent is a maximal consecutive block of up-steps whose matching down-steps all belong to the same descent.
%H A394944 Yu Hin Au and Murray R. Bremner, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.25731">Enumerating Multi-Operator Monomials in Commutative and Noncommutative Settings</a>, arXiv:2604.25731 [math.CO], 2026. See pp. 4, 19 (Table 4).
%F A394944 G.f.: 1 + (1 - x - 4*x^2 + 6*x^4 - 4*x^6 + x^8 - sqrt((1-x-4*x^2+6*x^4-4*x^6+x^8)^2 - 4*x*(4*x^2 - 6*x^4 + 4*x^6 - x^8))) / (2*(4*x^2 - 6*x^4 + 4*x^6 - x^8)) = 1 + A(x).
%F A394944 G.f. satisfies A(x) = x + x*A(x) + (4*x^2 - 6*x^4 + 4*x^6 - x^8)*(A(x) + A(x)^2).
%F A394944 a(n) = f(n-1) + 4*f(n-2) - 6*f(n-4) + 4*f(n-6) - f(n-8)
%F A394944        + 4*Sum_{k=1..n-3} a(k)*a(n-2-k)
%F A394944        - 6*Sum_{k=1..n-5} a(k)*a(n-4-k)
%F A394944        + 4*Sum_{k=1..n-7} a(k)*a(n-6-k)
%F A394944        - Sum_{k=1..n-9} a(k)*a(n-8-k)
%F A394944        with a(0)=a(1)=1 where f(n)=a(n) for n>=1 and f(n)=0 for n<=0.
%e A394944 a(5)=35 = 1 + 24 + 10: one word with no unary operators, namely *****; 24 words with one unary operator, namely P_i(**)*, *P_i(**), P_i(***), P_i(*)**, *P_i(*)*, **P_i(*) for i=1,2,3,4; and 10 canonical double-unary words P_i(P_j(*)) with 1<=i<=j<=4.
%Y A394944 Cf. A004148, A394942, A394943, A394941.
